=== Phase 2c refactors applied (no behavior change) ===
1. load-vault-config.ts — collapsed nested if/else FsError dispatch into a
   single conditional. The two redundant `path-not-found` branches now share
   one return statement; only `permission` is special-cased to permission-denied.
2. stages.ts — extracted shared `ParsedNote` type. Previously duplicated
   inline in scan-vault.ts and pipeline.ts; now defined once and imported
   by both. No behavioral change; ports retain identical signatures.
3. scan-vault.ts — replaced inline `import("...").Body / Frontmatter` casts
   with named imports at the top of the file. Improves readability without
   altering the runtime cast behavior.
4. initialize-capture.ts — removed obsolete docstring paragraph that
   referenced the now-corrected regex test (the Phase 2a test fix made the
   note stale).

=== Test correction note (Phase 2a iteration-2 scaffolding fix) ===
During Phase 2b, identified that step4-initialize-capture.test.ts:337
contained a regex `/-\d+$/` that was mathematically impossible to satisfy
with REQ-011 spec format `YYYY-MM-DD-HHmmss-SSS` (the trailing `-SSS`
millis segment always matches). Replaced with anchored positive assertion
/^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}-\d{6}-\d{3}$/ to validate exact base format. The
implementation matches the spec faithfully.

